COLOUR. Ground colour yellowish. Eyepatches dark blue. Antennae and lateral margin of head and Th. II with blue pigment. A longitudinal blue stripe present along midline from head to Th. II. Th. III with a broad transverse blue stripe. Abd. II with scattered pigment laterally and Abd. III with a very narrow blue stripe posteriorly.Abd. IV with two irregular transverse blue stripes. Coxae and tibiotarsi with weak pigment (
Fig. 1A–B
).

HEAD
. Antenna 0.47–0.63 times as long as body. Antennal segments ratio as I: II: III: IV = 1.00:1.28– 1.72: 1.28–1.65: 1.84–2.57. Distal part of Ant. IV with many sensory chaetae, normal ciliate chaetae and apical bulb bilobed (
Fig. 2A
). Lateral process (l.p.) of labial palp curved with tip not reaching apex of same papilla (
Fig. 2B
). Subapical chaeta of maxillary outer lobe subequal to apical one, 3 smooth hairs on sublobal plate (
Fig. 2C
). Labial chaetae 
